<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Odoo Open Treasures (Записи о xml)</title><link>http://blog.odooist.com/</link><description></description><atom:link href="http://blog.odooist.com/ru/categories/xml.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>ru</language><copyright>Contents © 2019 &lt;a href="mailto:odooist@gmail.com"&gt;Odooist&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Fri, 15 Nov 2019 13:39:19 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>New xpath element named "move"</title><link>http://blog.odooist.com/ru/posts/new-xpath-element-named-move/</link><dc:creator>Odooist</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The position='move' has been introduced to move an element in an inherited
view.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It's used as&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code xml"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_ed861d5a71154b2c86d37e7c2cf60650-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;xpath&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;expr=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"//@target"&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;position=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"after"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_ed861d5a71154b2c86d37e7c2cf60650-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;    &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;xpath&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;expr=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"//@node"&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;position=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"move"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_ed861d5a71154b2c86d37e7c2cf60650-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;/xpath&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;Or also:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code xml"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_e1ba04abecb34c5086ab9abb8e41b33b-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;field&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;name=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"target_field"&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;position=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"after"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_e1ba04abecb34c5086ab9abb8e41b33b-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;    &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;field&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;name=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"my_field"&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;position=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"move"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_e1ba04abecb34c5086ab9abb8e41b33b-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;/field&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;The xpath with a position after, before, inside or replace can thus now
have another xpath as direct child with position move.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>http://blog.odooist.com/ru/posts/new-xpath-element-named-move/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 15 Nov 2019 13:37:56 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>